- Intro to YAML :


	- Key Value Pair in YAML :

		Fruit: Apple 
		Vegetable: Carrot 
		Liquid: Water 
		Meat: Chicken 

	- Array/Lists in YAML :
		
		Fruits: 
		- Orange 
		- Apple 
		- Banana 

		Vegetables: 
		- Carrot 
		- Cauliflower 
		- Tomato 

	- Dictionary in YAML :

	Banana: 
		Calories: 105 		<<<< The spaces should be equal for all the elements in the YAML
		Fat: 0.4 g 
		Carbs: 27 g 
	Grapes: 
		Calories: 62 
		Fat: 0.3 g 
		Carbs: 16 g 



	- List containing dictionary containing Lists :

	Fruits: 							<<<< List of fruits
		- Banana: 						<<<< These are dictionary
			Calories: 105 
			Fat: 0.4 g 
			Carbs: 27 g 
		- Grape: 
			Calories: 62 
			Fat: 0.3 g 
			Carbs: 16 g 


	- When to use a dictionary or a List :

		- To start information of a single object we use dictionary.

			Color: Blue
			Model:
				Name: Corvette			<<<< Dictionary within a dictionary
				Year: 1995
			Transmission: Manual
			Price: $20,000


		- To store the collection of Cars we will use Lists of Dictionaries

		  - Color: Blue 
			Model: 
				Name: Corvette 
				Model: 1995 
			Transmission : Manual 
			Price: $20,080 
		  - Color: Grey 
			Model: 
				Name: Corvette 
				Model: 1995 
			Transmission: Manual 
			Price: $22,800 
		  - Color: Red 
			Model: 
				Name: Corvette 
				Model: 1995 
			Transmission : Automatic 
			Price: $20,800 
		  - Color: Green 
		  	Model: 
		  		Name: Corvette 
		  		Model: 1995 
		  	Transmission : Manual 
		  	Price: $23,008 
		  - Color: Blue 
		  	Model: 
		  		Name: Corvette 
		  		Model: 1995
		  	Transmission: Manual
		  	Price: $20,000


		- Dictionary are unordered collection

			Banana:								Banana:
				Calories: 105						Fat: 0.4g
				Fat: 0.4g			==				Calories: 105
				Carbs: 27g							Carbs: 27g


		- Lists are ordered collection

			Fruits:								Fruits:
			-  Orange							-	Orange
			-  Apple				!=			-	Apple
			-  Banana							-	Banana


		# -- is a comment in YAML